<i>The things I do are never forgiven</i>
<i>And just when I'm living them down</i>

71
00:07:17,117 --> 00:07:20,314
<i>I hear music, then I'm through</i>

72
00:07:20,487 --> 00:07:23,615
<i>'Cause music makes me do the things</i>
<i>I never should do</i>

73
00:07:23,790 --> 00:07:26,884
<i>When I hear music</i>

74
00:07:54,687 --> 00:07:56,587
Hey, Rog.

75
00:07:56,756 --> 00:07:59,554
Go easy, will you?
Don't bite the job that feeds you.

76
00:07:59,726 --> 00:08:01,091
Just what am I doing?

77
00:08:01,261 --> 00:08:05,823
That Swiss bell ringer is on the level
about not fooling with the cash customers.

78
00:08:15,408 --> 00:08:17,501
Hold your hats, boys.
Here we go again.

79
00:08:17,677 --> 00:08:19,804
The Latin type.

80
00:08:20,747 --> 00:08:25,707
Belinha, my head aches so badly.
I think I will go and eat an aspirin.

81
00:08:25,885 --> 00:08:29,616
You will excuse me.
Do not rise.

82
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:33,721
- Titia, shall I go with you?
- No, stay.

83
00:08:33,893 --> 00:08:37,056
But while I am gone
please do not introduce to Belinha...

84
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:40,290
...too many American customs.

85
00:08:43,636 --> 00:08:45,194
Rog.

86
00:08:45,371 --> 00:08:46,895
Hey, Rog.

87
00:08:47,874 --> 00:08:49,501
The last time you had that look...

88
00:08:49,676 --> 00:08:53,874
...all we had to live on for two weeks
was a can of prepared dog food.

89
00:08:55,048 --> 00:08:57,482
His father owns
the sunny side of Wall Street.

90
00:08:57,650 --> 00:08:59,345
And writes the preferred list.

91
00:08:59,519 --> 00:09:03,148
They say if he'd only give up airplanes,
songwriting and leading orchestras...

92
00:09:03,323 --> 00:09:05,348
...that he could name his own figure.

93
00:09:05,525 --> 00:09:08,494
He could name mine any time.

94
00:09:08,661 --> 00:09:13,064
You know, if a Brazilian girl
was half as interested in him as you are...

95
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:15,827
...and had half your freedom...

96
00:09:16,002 --> 00:09:18,835
...she'd...
- She'd what?

97
00:09:19,339 --> 00:09:23,139
- She'd get him over here, just for you.
- Oh, yeah?

98
00:09:23,309 --> 00:09:25,800
You mean, she'd try?

99
00:09:27,046 --> 00:09:28,638
Watch me.

100
00:09:49,168 --> 00:09:51,864
Oh, Rog.

101
00:09:52,038 --> 00:09:53,437
What is he doing now?

102
00:09:53,606 --> 00:09:56,166
He just fell into the trombone.

103
00:09:56,442 --> 00:09:59,969
You'd better have a heart, Belinha.
You'll break up the whole orchestra.

104
00:10:00,747 --> 00:10:04,774
Whenever a Brazilian girl starts something,
she must finish it.

105
00:10:08,121 --> 00:10:09,588
- Yes, madam?
- A pencil.

106
00:10:09,756 --> 00:10:10,882
Yes.

107
00:10:11,824 --> 00:10:13,382
Thank you.

108
00:10:26,706 --> 00:10:28,640
Remember the dog food.

109
00:10:28,808 --> 00:10:31,675
And it was the kind
they made out of fish.

110
00:10:32,412 --> 00:10:34,277
Mr. Bond?

111
00:10:34,981 --> 00:10:38,815
For you, sir.
From the lady, sir. The dark one.

112
00:10:49,996 --> 00:10:52,157
After all, look at her.
What have I got to lose?

113
00:10:52,332 --> 00:10:53,321
Only 20 jobs.

114
00:10:53,499 --> 00:10:56,161
Since when is dancing a familiarity?

115
00:10:57,537 --> 00:11:00,370
Perhaps it's a formal resignation.

116
00:11:10,350 --> 00:11:12,409
She's smiling at him.

117
00:11:20,393 --> 00:11:24,853
What have these South Americans got
below the equator that we haven't?

118
00:12:13,012 --> 00:12:15,480
- Excuse me, sir...
- Tell Senhora De Rezende...

119
00:12:15,648 --> 00:12:18,583
...that her niece is dancing
with the orchestra leader.

120
00:12:18,751 --> 00:12:21,049
Hurry, please.

121
00:12:21,387 --> 00:12:24,550
Oh, waiter, tell De Rezende
that Belinha is dancing with a musician.

122
00:12:24,724 --> 00:12:26,589
- Yes, sir.
- Go on. Make it snappy.

123
00:12:26,759 --> 00:12:30,058
Here, boy, tell Rezende
the kid is dancing with the drummer.

124
00:12:30,229 --> 00:12:32,026
Okay, pop.

125
00:12:35,134 --> 00:12:38,331
Tell the old sea lion that baby
is hoofing with a piccolo player.

126
00:12:40,373 --> 00:12:43,171
- Oh, madam. Oh, madam.
- Yes?

127
00:12:43,342 --> 00:12:45,708
Mademoiselle is going in a big way
for a gigolo.

128
00:12:45,878 --> 00:12:48,904
Belinha? A gigolo?

129
00:12:52,852 --> 00:12:54,581
My niece.

130
00:12:58,157 --> 00:12:59,886
Is it possible?

131
00:13:00,059 --> 00:13:04,462
The flower of the womanhood of the
Alves Lima De Castro Pimenta De Rezende.

132
00:13:05,531 --> 00:13:07,522
Isn't it terrible?

133
00:13:11,704 --> 00:13:13,262
Titia.

134
00:13:13,439 --> 00:13:15,600
- This is my aunt.
- Oh, how do you do?

135
00:13:15,775 --> 00:13:18,642
My niece thanks you for your politeness,
young man.

136
00:13:18,811 --> 00:13:22,941
She will not require
any more of your services this afternoon.

137
00:13:25,952 --> 00:13:27,419
Is the usual rate higher?

138
00:13:28,087 --> 00:13:29,987
I am not familiar with such matters.

139
00:13:30,156 --> 00:13:34,149
No, no. It's quite all right.
It's very generous.

140
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:37,327
I think. Oh, just a moment.

141
00:13:38,464 --> 00:13:40,227
- Thank you, sir.
- With my compliments.

142
00:13:41,234 --> 00:13:44,294
The quaint young man
has given me an orchid.

143
00:13:47,406 --> 00:13:51,172
In my country they grow like weeds,
you know.

144
00:13:51,677 --> 00:13:53,144
Come, Belinha.

145
00:13:53,312 --> 00:13:58,841
Senhora, would your niece prefer
a geranium? Or a begonia, perhaps?

146
00:14:29,182 --> 00:14:33,642
Pull in your apples, boys.
Here comes William Tell.

147
00:14:45,865 --> 00:14:47,594
Well, Roger's done it again.

148
00:14:47,767 --> 00:14:51,760
Yeah, and just as I was getting
caught up with my alimony too.

149
00:14:51,938 --> 00:14:56,898
That Sir Galahad has gotten us kicked out
of every job from Maine to Miami.

150
00:14:57,076 --> 00:14:59,203
I wonder where we go from here.

151
00:14:59,378 --> 00:15:02,677
Heads we go north,
and tails we go south.

152
00:15:02,848 --> 00:15:04,509
And the quarter goes to the bellhop.

153
00:15:04,684 --> 00:15:07,585
- Hey, that's my case two bits.
- Here comes Fred.

154
00:15:07,753 --> 00:15:10,244
Boys, boys and girls,
and you too, Honey.

155
00:15:10,423 --> 00:15:12,015
Have I got a surprise for you?

156
00:15:12,191 --> 00:15:14,591
- It couldn't be money.
- Well, what is it?

157
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,285
Wait a minute, wait a minute.
This is really good news.

158
00:15:17,463 --> 00:15:19,124
Rog has outdone himself.

159
00:15:19,298 --> 00:15:22,631
I'll bet he's broken both legs running after
two women at the same time.

160
00:15:22,802 --> 00:15:25,635
Nothing of the kind.
He's landed us a job in Rio.

161
00:15:25,805 --> 00:15:28,831
Rio de Janeiro.
The Hotel Atlantico.

162
00:15:29,008 --> 00:15:34,275
- We'll be flying down any morning now.
- And swimming back in the afternoon.

163
00:15:34,447 --> 00:15:36,244
I'm taking my water wings.

164
00:15:36,916 --> 00:15:39,282
Will one of you boys pass out
these salary checks?

165
00:15:39,452 --> 00:15:40,942
- Gladly.
- I said one of you.

166
00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:42,314
Well, I can pass them out.

167
00:15:42,488 --> 00:15:45,480
Here, Eddie, you do it.
Get in line, you guys.

168
00:16:24,830 --> 00:16:27,196
Oh, I beg your par...

169
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:31,398
- Good morning.
- Mr. Bond, I'm so sorry.

170
00:16:31,570 --> 00:16:34,300
- I had no idea I was making trouble.
- Think nothing of it.

171
00:16:34,473 --> 00:16:38,569
I'm just accepting a new engagement,
and not to dance either.

172
00:16:38,744 --> 00:16:41,975
Please don't be angry with me.

173
00:16:42,148 --> 00:16:43,911
I'm sorry.

174
00:16:50,323 --> 00:16:51,415
I must send this.

175
00:16:51,590 --> 00:16:54,491
You see, we missed the plane
to Rio de Janeiro...

176
00:16:54,927 --> 00:16:57,327
...on account of Titia's headache.

177
00:16:57,496 --> 00:17:02,433
- Did you say Rio de Janeiro?
- Yes.

178
00:17:02,601 --> 00:17:06,367
Father is not so well
and wants me there right away.

179
00:17:06,605 --> 00:17:09,403
What a strange coincidence.

180
00:17:10,776 --> 00:17:11,834
It happens...

181
00:17:12,011 --> 00:17:15,970
It just so happens that I have a friend
who's flying his own plane down south.

182
00:17:16,148 --> 00:17:17,979
How far is he going?

183
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:20,516
Just as far as you want him to.

184
00:17:20,686 --> 00:17:26,056
If he could fly me to Port-au-Prince, I could
still catch this morning's plane to Rio.

185
00:17:26,225 --> 00:17:27,692
Do you think he'd take me?

186
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:29,487
Take you?

187
00:17:29,662 --> 00:17:31,755
Well, I think I could persuade him.

188
00:17:31,931 --> 00:17:33,796
Oh, how nice of you.

189
00:17:33,966 --> 00:17:36,298
I'll go right up
and tell Titia to pack at once.

190
00:17:36,469 --> 00:17:40,303
No, just a moment. You see...

191
00:17:40,473 --> 00:17:45,240
...my friend's plane is very small,
and it only has room for one passenger.

192
00:17:45,411 --> 00:17:48,744
- Oh, dear.
- Are you afraid your aunt won't let you?

193
00:17:48,914 --> 00:17:52,077
She'd have to for Father's sake.

194
00:17:52,251 --> 00:17:53,548
Dear Father.

195
00:17:53,719 --> 00:17:56,688
Titia can take the next plane.
I'll tell her.

196
00:18:02,928 --> 00:18:06,227
- Hi, Rog. Everything all set?
- I hope so, baby. I hope so.

197
00:18:06,399 --> 00:18:10,392
Shall I lay out your heliotrope coveralls,
or the pink ones with the tan grease spots?

198
00:18:11,103 --> 00:18:14,698
Well, I usually fly with you, don't I?
Or am I just a fly in the carburetor?

199
00:18:14,874 --> 00:18:17,570
Well, I tell you, Freddy, old man,
you see, it's this way:

200
00:18:17,743 --> 00:18:21,543
I met a friend, a very old friend
who asked me as a very special favor.

201
00:18:21,714 --> 00:18:24,410
You know how it is.
You'll have to fly down with the boys.

202
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:28,019
You don't mind, do you? See they
have a dill pickle with their box lunch.

203
00:18:28,187 --> 00:18:31,418
Oh, and send this wire saying
we're coming, and I'll see you in Rio.

204
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:32,989
"Flying Down to Rio."

205
00:18:33,159 --> 00:18:35,320
Boy, what a title for a new song.
You like that?

206
00:18:35,494 --> 00:18:36,927
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

207
00:18:37,096 --> 00:18:38,996
And the very name
for that new number too.

208
00:18:39,165 --> 00:18:40,291
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

209
00:18:40,466 --> 00:18:42,798
Well, see you in Rio, boy.

210
00:18:43,602 --> 00:18:45,229
Yeah.

211
00:18:56,182 --> 00:18:59,083
Is this the plane of the gentleman
who is taking a lady to Rio?

212
00:18:59,251 --> 00:19:03,347
Yes, ma'am. If you're the lady who expects
to go to Rio with the gentleman in the plane.

213
00:19:03,522 --> 00:19:04,853
My niece is going.

214
00:19:05,024 --> 00:19:08,187
- Kindly conduct us.
- Yes, ma'am. Right this way.

215
00:19:10,229 --> 00:19:12,390
Are you the conductor?

216
00:19:12,565 --> 00:19:15,033
Have you the proper credentials?

217
00:19:17,336 --> 00:19:19,167
Are you married?

218
00:19:21,207 --> 00:19:23,300
You have children?

219
00:19:26,779 --> 00:19:31,341
Why does he not speak?
Is he a deaf mute, or only dumb?

220
00:19:31,517 --> 00:19:34,145
Please, Titia, he's doing us a favor.

221
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:37,118
I don't know.
He does not appear to be quite right.

222
00:19:37,289 --> 00:19:39,223
Perhaps I'd better go along.

223
00:19:39,391 --> 00:19:42,360
No, you can't. You see, it won't fly
with more than two aboard.

224
00:19:42,528 --> 00:19:45,554
Here we go.
Step right up, miss.

225
00:19:46,765 --> 00:19:48,630
There we are.

226
00:19:49,201 --> 00:19:52,637
- Wait, I have not kissed my niece yet.
- Don't worry, lady.

227
00:19:52,805 --> 00:19:54,272
He'll take care of that for you.

228
00:19:54,440 --> 00:19:59,844
Belinha, do not speak to him
unless it is absolutely necessary.

229
00:20:10,789 --> 00:20:14,725
Oh, dear me. Something tells me
I should never have let her go.

230
00:20:14,894 --> 00:20:18,352
Rodriguez, get them down.
Go after them.

231
00:20:18,531 --> 00:20:21,967
Senhora De Rezende,
I was a good coachman.

232
00:20:22,134 --> 00:20:27,128
You made of me a chauffeur,
but you cannot expect me to be an eagle.

233
00:20:34,647 --> 00:20:39,084
Do I have to fly all the way to Haiti
on a piano bench?

234
00:20:42,454 --> 00:20:44,149
Do l...?

235
00:21:06,545 --> 00:21:09,343
<i>Just a gigolo</i>

236
00:21:10,849 --> 00:21:13,374
<i>Everywhere I go</i>

237
00:22:05,604 --> 00:22:08,004
Was that a close shave.

238
00:22:17,783 --> 00:22:21,549
Wasn't it fortunate this
convenient beach was at your disposal...

239
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,052
...when the motor went wrong?

240
00:22:35,968 --> 00:22:40,632
Or perhaps your plane always makes a forced
landing when you have a lady passenger?

241
00:22:43,876 --> 00:22:46,367
I don't think it's anything serious.

242
00:22:46,845 --> 00:22:49,006
Probably just the gas line.

243
00:22:49,181 --> 00:22:50,580
We should be off in no time.

244
00:22:52,117 --> 00:22:54,881
I'll believe you
when we're in the air again.

245
00:23:21,914 --> 00:23:25,680
- So you're going to be a sap and fix it, huh?
- What?

246
00:23:25,851 --> 00:23:29,787
When was there a better opportunity
for dirty work at the crossroads?

247
00:23:29,955 --> 00:23:33,914
Throw away a part of the motor.
She'll never know the difference.

248
00:23:34,359 --> 00:23:37,920
Listen, your suggestions have been
getting me into messes all my life.

249
00:23:38,097 --> 00:23:40,497
And I'm the one who ends up
getting his face slapped.

250
00:23:40,666 --> 00:23:45,899
All right, but don't keep reminding me
of the opportunity you missed.

251
00:23:46,705 --> 00:23:50,698
Well, I suppose I'll never hear the end of it
unless I do as you say.

252
00:24:00,252 --> 00:24:02,914
This is gonna be more serious
than I thought.

253
00:24:06,091 --> 00:24:09,185
Of course he's deliberately
trying to keep you here.

254
00:24:09,361 --> 00:24:11,921
That's why he picked a deserted island.

255
00:24:12,097 --> 00:24:13,860
Isn't that what you want?

256
00:24:14,032 --> 00:24:16,500
I can't let him know that.

257
00:24:16,668 --> 00:24:20,365
After all, I must maintain my reserve.

258
00:24:20,773 --> 00:24:22,798
You and your reserve.

259
00:24:22,975 --> 00:24:28,242
If people knew you as I do,
they might be a little bit shocked.

260
00:24:31,116 --> 00:24:33,949
Now give her your bag of tricks.
You know how we always do it.

261
00:24:34,119 --> 00:24:36,087
Start with your music.

262
00:24:36,789 --> 00:24:41,453
- I don't think she'll fall for that old line.
- We haven't met one yet who didn't.

263
00:24:46,098 --> 00:24:47,326
What will I play?

264
00:24:47,499 --> 00:24:51,765
Can't you get an inspiration
by just looking at her? Look at her.

265
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:55,973
She's like an orchid.

266
00:24:57,509 --> 00:25:00,569
And there's the moonlight.
"Orchids in the Moonlight."

267
00:25:00,746 --> 00:25:03,681
There, I've given you
another title for a song.

268
00:26:30,869 --> 00:26:33,565
If they only understood themselves
as we do.

269
00:26:33,739 --> 00:26:36,970
Isn't it silly how humans deny themselves
the things they want most?

270
00:26:37,142 --> 00:26:42,011
To satisfy stupid convention.
But we can speak the truth.

271
00:26:42,180 --> 00:26:43,613
I can say I love you.

272
00:26:59,164 --> 00:27:03,430
Oh, I didn't mean this.
I don't know how it happened.

273
00:27:03,602 --> 00:27:07,629
What difference does it make?
It happened, isn't that enough?

274
00:27:12,411 --> 00:27:15,403
No, you don't understand.

275
00:27:15,580 --> 00:27:17,810
I haven't the right.

276
00:27:20,619 --> 00:27:22,678
My life has long been arranged.

277
00:27:27,859 --> 00:27:31,761
Don't tell me anything so 18th-century
as a family arrangement could...

278
00:27:31,930 --> 00:27:34,990
We do things so in my country.

279
00:27:38,103 --> 00:27:41,766
Then I'm going to institute
some radical changes in your country.

280
00:27:43,675 --> 00:27:46,974
But my fiancé has even built me
a beautiful home on Rio bay.

281
00:27:47,145 --> 00:27:49,204
But you love me.

282
00:27:49,448 --> 00:27:52,975
- You're taking a lot for granted.
- And I love you.

283
00:27:53,518 --> 00:27:56,919
You don't even know my name.
You must forget tonight.

284
00:27:57,089 --> 00:27:59,114
Now you're talking a lot for granted.

285
00:27:59,291 --> 00:28:01,452
I'm determined
that you'll never see me again.

286
00:28:01,626 --> 00:28:04,823
If I have to turn the country upside down,
I'll see you.

287
00:28:04,997 --> 00:28:08,228
- I won't permit you.
- We'll see about that.

288
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:11,665
- You'll do just as I say.
- Oh, will I?

289
00:28:12,037 --> 00:28:13,800
- You will.
- I will not.

290
00:28:13,972 --> 00:28:17,908
Your family, your fiancé, the army, the navy,
and all of South America can't stop me.

291
00:28:18,076 --> 00:28:20,544
And if you're silly enough to think that...

292
00:28:23,915 --> 00:28:25,348
I've stood about enough from you.

293
00:28:49,875 --> 00:28:51,775
Oh, miss.

294
00:28:54,312 --> 00:28:56,837
Oh, miss.

295
00:28:58,450 --> 00:29:00,042
Good morning.

296
00:29:03,121 --> 00:29:06,147
I'm just going down to the corner drugstore
to get some breakfast.

297
00:29:06,324 --> 00:29:09,555
Is there any special way
you like your coconut juice?

298
00:29:10,762 --> 00:29:12,252
Say, listen...

299
00:29:12,431 --> 00:29:16,094
...l'm not going to spend the rest
of my days with a dumb wife.

300
00:29:20,472 --> 00:29:24,465
Well, if you're going to act that way,
I've got some looking around to do.

301
00:29:53,872 --> 00:29:55,703
Mr. Bond.

302
00:29:56,441 --> 00:30:00,605
Mr. Bond, where are you?
Where are you?

303
00:30:00,912 --> 00:30:03,005
Roger, where are you?
Where have you gone?

304
00:30:03,181 --> 00:30:05,046
- What's the matter?
- Wild men. Cannibals.

305
00:30:05,217 --> 00:30:07,014
Where?

306
00:30:07,419 --> 00:30:11,947
Roger. Roger, darling. Roger.

307
00:30:12,724 --> 00:30:14,453
What happened?

308
00:30:15,093 --> 00:30:16,890
I don't know.

309
00:30:30,108 --> 00:30:31,507
Oh, I say.

310
00:30:31,676 --> 00:30:33,871
I beg your pardon, sir...

311
00:30:34,045 --> 00:30:36,639
...but it is strictly
against the rules to move the ball.

312
00:30:39,684 --> 00:30:42,551
Say, what kind of
a desert island is this, anyway?

313
00:30:42,721 --> 00:30:45,281
- Where are we?
- This is Haiti, sir.

314
00:30:45,457 --> 00:30:47,448
Port-au-Prince Golf Club.

315
00:30:47,626 --> 00:30:50,026
I was availing myself
an early morning practice...

316
00:30:50,195 --> 00:30:53,358
...for the caddy's tournament, sir.
- But I saw wild men.

317
00:30:57,002 --> 00:30:59,061
The bellhops taking their morning dip.

318
00:31:00,739 --> 00:31:03,708
Wild men, fancy that.

319
00:31:04,042 --> 00:31:08,138
Say, is there any place near here
where I can get a mechanic to fix my plane?

320
00:31:08,313 --> 00:31:12,215
Oh, certainly, sir.
The airport's a five-minute jaunt from here.

321
00:31:12,384 --> 00:31:15,410
If you'll listen, you can hear them
warming up the Rio plane.

322
00:31:15,587 --> 00:31:17,384
We caught up
with yesterday's plane?

323
00:31:17,556 --> 00:31:20,047
Oh, yes, sir.
It spends the night here.

324
00:31:21,259 --> 00:31:23,352
- It leaves in 10 minutes.
- Splendid.

325
00:31:23,528 --> 00:31:26,827
I'll get my bag and take the Rio plane
the rest of the way.

326
00:31:26,998 --> 00:31:32,095
Thank you so much for the lift, Mr. Bond.
It was lovely of you. Goodbye.

327
00:31:32,270 --> 00:31:35,364
- Come.
- Right-o.

328
00:31:35,540 --> 00:31:38,703
Say, wait a minute.
I can fix my plane in a jiffy.

329
00:31:44,516 --> 00:31:47,144
- To Rio.
- Right-o.

330
00:31:51,389 --> 00:31:54,222
If you're looking for the part
of your motor you threw away...

331
00:31:54,392 --> 00:31:57,190
...you'll find it on top of the piano.

332
00:33:04,696 --> 00:33:08,632
Oh, this isn't just another girl, Julio.
This is the real thing.

333
00:33:08,800 --> 00:33:11,064
Old man cupid
didn't fire an arrow this time.

334
00:33:11,236 --> 00:33:13,704
No, sir. He sunk a harpoon.

335
00:33:13,872 --> 00:33:17,399
- So this time it's a Brazilian girl?
- And what a Brazilian girl.

336
00:33:17,575 --> 00:33:21,773
I'm goofy about her.
I am crazy for her.

337
00:33:21,946 --> 00:33:23,846
As a matter of fact, I like her.

338
00:33:24,015 --> 00:33:27,314
I met her in Miami at the Hibiscus Hotel.

339
00:33:27,585 --> 00:33:31,681
Yes, she was traveling
with one of those Dona Elenas.

340
00:33:32,691 --> 00:33:34,420
And talk about luck.

341
00:33:34,592 --> 00:33:39,222
The day you sent for me, her father got
sick and she had to hurry back here to Rio.

342
00:33:40,398 --> 00:33:43,060
And you'll be seeing her here, of course?

343
00:33:43,234 --> 00:33:47,568
No, that's the catch.
She wouldn't tell me her name or address.

344
00:33:47,739 --> 00:33:49,001
Then it's all on your side.

345
00:33:49,174 --> 00:33:51,506
In a pig's monocle.
She's dizzy about me.

346
00:33:51,676 --> 00:33:52,938
Did she tell you so?

347
00:33:53,111 --> 00:33:55,739
She didn't have to tell me.
I can take a hint.

348
00:33:55,914 --> 00:33:58,041
I tell you, Julio, she is exquisite.

349
00:33:58,216 --> 00:34:02,243
She has a face like a flower, a rose.

350
00:34:02,420 --> 00:34:05,355
What am I talking about?
She's like an orchid, a white orchid.

351
00:34:06,691 --> 00:34:09,626
- She sounds enchanting.
- Enchanting, bewildering.

352
00:34:09,794 --> 00:34:12,490
Bewitching, intoxicating, devastating.

353
00:34:12,664 --> 00:34:16,725
I tell you, Julio, every time I think about her
I want to bite myself, and that's news.

354
00:34:19,571 --> 00:34:23,063
She has beautiful black hair
and big brown eyes, eh, Roger?

355
00:34:23,241 --> 00:34:27,143
How true, how true.
And has she got:

356
00:34:30,615 --> 00:34:33,948
And when she smiles
there's a funny little curve to her mouth?

357
00:34:34,119 --> 00:34:36,587
That's right.
But how would you know?

358
00:34:37,188 --> 00:34:41,056
And, Julio, that wonderful night
we spent on the beach together.

359
00:34:41,226 --> 00:34:46,562
Just the two of us alone,
not a soul for miles and miles.

360
00:34:52,470 --> 00:34:56,065
- Was there a moon?
- A glorious moon.

361
00:34:56,241 --> 00:34:58,300
There would be a moon.

362
00:34:58,476 --> 00:35:01,445
- It all comes back to me now.
- Yes?

363
00:35:01,613 --> 00:35:03,740
- I took her passionately in my arms.
- Yes?

364
00:35:03,915 --> 00:35:06,679
- And as I drew her to me...
- Yes?

365
00:35:06,851 --> 00:35:08,716
No, it was too beautiful.

366
00:35:09,254 --> 00:35:11,449
Too sacred to talk about.

367
00:35:11,623 --> 00:35:15,252
Roger, what happened after you took her
passionately in your arms...

368
00:35:15,427 --> 00:35:17,520
...and drew her to you?

369
00:35:18,196 --> 00:35:22,132
- That's when I ran into difficulties.
- Difficulties?

370
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:26,168
It seems the poor kid is already engaged
to some local cluck...

371
00:35:26,337 --> 00:35:29,067
...who signed her before
she knew any better.

372
00:35:30,942 --> 00:35:34,036
A poor, defenseless child
in a baby buggy.

373
00:35:34,212 --> 00:35:37,010
And now the mug is trying
to hold her to it...

374
00:35:37,182 --> 00:35:41,710
...by squawking about some shack he's
knocked together for her on the waterfront.

375
00:35:42,220 --> 00:35:45,621
- Did you ever hear of a heel like that?
- No.

376
00:35:46,057 --> 00:35:47,581
Thanks.

377
00:35:48,193 --> 00:35:50,821
Julio, I want you to do something for me.

378
00:35:50,995 --> 00:35:52,690
I want you to help me find her.

379
00:35:52,864 --> 00:35:54,764
- Who, me?
- Yeah.

380
00:35:54,933 --> 00:35:57,458
Oh, no, Roger. I could not do that.

381
00:35:57,635 --> 00:36:00,536
- With us an engagement is very serious.
- Serious?

382
00:36:00,705 --> 00:36:04,402
Don't you think it's serious when every time
I think of her I wanna bite myself?

383
00:36:04,576 --> 00:36:07,636
Boy, am I suffering.
Well, here's to her.

384
00:36:07,812 --> 00:36:09,177
And happiness.

385
00:36:09,347 --> 00:36:12,407
Thanks, old man. Thanks a lot.

386
00:36:13,852 --> 00:36:17,811
Hey, Rog? Oh, Rog, the boys are downstairs.
We're waiting for you.

387
00:36:17,989 --> 00:36:20,583
Hey, hey, no more
of that bathroom drinking.

388
00:36:22,093 --> 00:36:24,926
Listen, we have to go and hear
the Turuna Turuna band tonight.

389
00:36:25,096 --> 00:36:27,360
I can't go hear anything.
I gotta go find someone.

390
00:36:27,532 --> 00:36:28,760
Go find someone?

391
00:36:29,367 --> 00:36:31,460
That look in his eye.

392
00:36:31,636 --> 00:36:33,228
You don't mean the senhorita?

393
00:36:33,404 --> 00:36:35,634
After that frosting you got in Miami?

394
00:36:35,807 --> 00:36:39,038
Boy, she made him look
like an angel cake.

395
00:36:39,210 --> 00:36:40,700
Well, I guess it's no use.

396
00:36:40,879 --> 00:36:43,211
I see you've got your hunting suit on.

397
00:36:43,381 --> 00:36:47,875
Say, keep out of jail, will you?
They throw the keys in the bay down here.

398
00:36:48,052 --> 00:36:52,386
So long, fella. Nice guy,
but he takes his work too seriously.

399
00:36:52,557 --> 00:36:54,787
Pardon me, Rog.
I must make a phone call.

400
00:36:54,959 --> 00:36:57,018
Sure, help yourself.
Make yourself at home.

401
00:36:57,962 --> 00:37:01,454
Julio. I was just thinking about you.

402
00:37:02,433 --> 00:37:05,425
But you're going to see me tomorrow night
at the Aviator's Club.

403
00:37:05,970 --> 00:37:07,665
I must see you tonight.

404
00:37:07,839 --> 00:37:09,101
It's very important.

405
00:37:09,674 --> 00:37:12,507
Wait, dear, I'll ask Titia.

406
00:37:12,677 --> 00:37:14,508
Julio wants to see me tonight.

407
00:37:15,613 --> 00:37:17,376
Have him come over.

408
00:37:19,083 --> 00:37:23,144
Julio, darling, I'm so sorry.
Titia says no.

409
00:37:23,321 --> 00:37:25,221
You see, we're so busy.

410
00:37:25,523 --> 00:37:28,014
You do understand, don't you?

411
00:37:28,192 --> 00:37:30,592
Oh, you're such a dear.

412
00:37:30,762 --> 00:37:32,286
Good night.

413
00:37:33,364 --> 00:37:35,889
We are so busy thinking
about a band leader.

414
00:37:42,373 --> 00:37:44,500
Darling, Titia...

415
00:37:44,676 --> 00:37:49,045
...you know I'd never do anything
to hurt Julio, don't you?

416
00:37:49,547 --> 00:37:53,950
But, darling, mayn't I have just a little fun
before I settle down...

417
00:37:54,118 --> 00:37:57,110
...and start having all of those thousands
of children?

418
00:37:57,288 --> 00:37:59,051
Belinha!

419
00:38:02,694 --> 00:38:03,956
What's the matter?

420
00:38:04,128 --> 00:38:06,926
- Didn't she have a friend for you?
- Yes. Oh, no.

421
00:38:07,098 --> 00:38:09,089
- We are just making some plans.
- No, thanks.

422
00:38:09,267 --> 00:38:12,361
There's going to be a ball
at the Aviator's Club tomorrow night.

423
00:38:12,537 --> 00:38:16,997
- I want you and Fred to be my guests.
- Swell. Maybe she'll be there.

424
00:38:17,175 --> 00:38:18,164
It's possible.

425
00:38:18,343 --> 00:38:21,278
Say, that would be a great place
to try out my new song.

426
00:38:21,446 --> 00:38:23,107
Listen, I'll show you how it goes.

427
00:38:23,615 --> 00:38:27,449
I call it "Orchids in the Moonlight."
I wrote it for her.

428
00:38:54,445 --> 00:38:57,209
- It's a nice cozy little spot you have here.
- Thank you.

429
00:38:57,382 --> 00:39:01,580
I personally myself
will escort you to your table.

430
00:39:01,753 --> 00:39:03,584
This way, please.

431
00:39:03,755 --> 00:39:06,383
I also have the honor to visit
your country once.

432
00:39:06,557 --> 00:39:08,115
I play vaudeville.

433
00:39:08,292 --> 00:39:12,228
I played Milwaukee, Cincinnati,
Newport News...

434
00:39:12,430 --> 00:39:14,990
...and Schenectady.

435
00:39:15,166 --> 00:39:16,428
- Schenectady?
- Yes.

436
00:39:16,601 --> 00:39:21,038
- You ever play Syracuse?
- Syracuse, sure. I play four, five times a day.

437
00:39:21,205 --> 00:39:24,902
- Nice work, if you can get it.
- Yes, and the most astonishing thing was...

438
00:39:25,076 --> 00:39:27,442
- Did you play there?
- Yes. No. Yes.

439
00:39:27,612 --> 00:39:30,445
The most astonishing was
that the audience always laughed.

440
00:39:30,615 --> 00:39:32,708
Laughed. You're telling us.

441
00:39:32,884 --> 00:39:35,876
I also have reserved those tables
for your Clippings.

442
00:39:36,054 --> 00:39:37,681
Clippers, if you don't mind.

443
00:39:37,855 --> 00:39:39,447
Yes, thank you, Clippings.

444
00:39:39,624 --> 00:39:43,151
And this table here, please.
This table for you.

445
00:39:43,361 --> 00:39:44,794
Senhorita, sit down.

446
00:39:44,962 --> 00:39:48,921
Now, I want you to admire
my greatest attraction, the Turunas.

447
00:39:52,303 --> 00:39:55,830
Turunas? They look like
a bunch of zombies to me.

448
00:39:56,007 --> 00:39:58,202
So that quartet's a band.

449
00:39:58,376 --> 00:40:00,606
Well, if that's our only competition...

450
00:40:00,778 --> 00:40:02,678
Don't hurt the old boy's feelings.

451
00:40:08,286 --> 00:40:12,985
We have some distinguished visitors
from our sister continent, North America.

452
00:40:13,157 --> 00:40:16,183
- Shall we play them a foxtrot?
- No, we want the Carioca.

453
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:18,624
- Play the Carioca.
- The Carioca. Play the Carioca.

454
00:40:19,297 --> 00:40:21,629
- Carioca.
- Why don't you play the Carioca?

455
00:40:24,135 --> 00:40:25,762
What's the matter
with the foxtrot?

456
00:40:25,937 --> 00:40:30,670
Pardon me, senhor. The American foxtrot
is considered too tame, too dull.

457
00:40:30,842 --> 00:40:33,970
- Our people prefer the Carioca.
- I see.

458
00:40:34,145 --> 00:40:38,707
- You mean, they prefer it in public?
- <i>Sí, senhorita.</i> Everybody in Rio.

459
00:40:41,052 --> 00:40:42,576
Very well, then.

460
00:40:43,187 --> 00:40:45,712
Boys, the Carioca.

461
00:40:57,235 --> 00:41:00,534
If that's all they can do, we're a cinch.
Our band will be a sensation.

462
00:42:02,934 --> 00:42:05,630
- Think they've got something.
- They have.

463
00:42:06,270 --> 00:42:08,670
This stuff is swell, but we can't do it.

464
00:42:22,653 --> 00:42:24,883
So that's the Carioca.

465
00:42:25,056 --> 00:42:30,084
- What's this business about the foreheads?
- Mental telepathy.

466
00:42:30,261 --> 00:42:32,729
I can tell what they're thinking
about from here.

467
