01:10:27,336 --> 01:10:29,361
Come, darling.

695
01:10:33,009 --> 01:10:35,739
Hey, Rog, we gotta do something
about this.

696
01:10:39,382 --> 01:10:40,781
And I know just what to do.

697
01:10:40,950 --> 01:10:42,747
- Where's Julio?
- At the Aviator's Club

698
01:10:42,919 --> 01:10:45,217
That's perfect.
Now, listen, this is terrific.

699
01:10:45,388 --> 01:10:48,846
If we can get all the members
of that organization to cooperate with us...

700
01:10:49,025 --> 01:10:50,890
...then the president of China
can't stop us.

701
01:11:05,041 --> 01:11:06,440
Back off, girls.

702
01:11:06,609 --> 01:11:08,338
- Everything fixed, Julio?
- Yes.

703
01:11:08,511 --> 01:11:10,376
- Hello, boy. Hello, babe.
- Hello.

704
01:11:10,546 --> 01:11:12,480
Oh, this is swell.
Look at all the planes.

705
01:11:12,648 --> 01:11:16,448
Behold. As you requested, the gentlemen
of the Aviator's Club at your service.

706
01:11:16,619 --> 01:11:17,847
Julio, you're marvelous.

707
01:11:18,020 --> 01:11:22,514
Now all we have to do is sales talk the girls
into coming across. Come on, let's go.

708
01:11:22,692 --> 01:11:26,287
And in conclusion, girls, I want to say
that I'm not asking anything of you...

709
01:11:26,462 --> 01:11:29,989
...that I wouldn't ask of my own sister.
Now, will you do it?

710
01:11:30,166 --> 01:11:31,929
I'll do it. Sounds like a new thrill.

711
01:11:32,101 --> 01:11:33,693
- Come on, girls.
- That's the stuff.

712
01:11:33,869 --> 01:11:35,302
So that's the way it is, girls.

713
01:11:35,471 --> 01:11:39,271
And I'm not holding a thing back. I know
you'll all come through. How's about it?

714
01:11:39,442 --> 01:11:41,672
- Okay with me.
- Why don't you do it yourself?

715
01:11:41,844 --> 01:11:44,210
That's just what I'm going to do,
you little witch.

716
01:11:44,380 --> 01:11:46,814
Come on, girls, let's go.

717
01:11:53,222 --> 01:11:56,123
It's a new game, girls,
and it's just too ducky for words.

718
01:11:56,292 --> 01:11:58,419
Now, let me see.

719
01:12:01,063 --> 01:12:03,759
Now, the rest of you girls
turn your backs.

720
01:12:03,933 --> 01:12:06,731
That's right.
Now, don't you dare peek.

721
01:12:06,902 --> 01:12:10,065
Oh, this is going to be more darn fun.

722
01:12:10,239 --> 01:12:12,571
- Blindman's bluff?
- That's right.

723
01:12:12,742 --> 01:12:16,439
- I thought so.
- Oh, you did, did you?

724
01:12:16,812 --> 01:12:20,612
See that they're all fastened on tight.
We don't want any slip-ups.

725
01:12:30,826 --> 01:12:32,157
All right, hold still, girls.

726
01:12:32,328 --> 01:12:35,161
- <i>Say, do you think it's safe?</i>
- <i>I hope these straps will hold.</i>

727
01:12:35,331 --> 01:12:38,698
<i>It's a good thing my parents</i>
<i>don't know about this.</i>

728
01:12:39,235 --> 01:12:41,897
<i>To think I'd ever come to this.</i>

729
01:12:42,438 --> 01:12:45,839
- <i>I don't know whether I like this.</i>
- <i>We can't make the same mistake twice.</i>

730
01:12:46,008 --> 01:12:49,205
- Up you go.
- Okay by me.

731
01:12:49,979 --> 01:12:53,073
Oh, not so tight, please.

732
01:12:55,017 --> 01:12:56,882
That hurts.

733
01:12:57,186 --> 01:13:00,678
<i>Something tells me</i>
<i>this is the wrong thing to do.</i>

734
01:13:00,956 --> 01:13:03,550
<i>I'll try anything once.</i>

735
01:13:03,959 --> 01:13:06,291
Senhor Bond, one moment
of your precious time.

736
01:13:06,462 --> 01:13:08,487
Senhor De Rezende send you this.

737
01:13:08,664 --> 01:13:10,325
Oh, thanks.

738
01:13:18,974 --> 01:13:20,839
Saint Christopher.

739
01:13:49,605 --> 01:13:52,335
I seem to have walked
into something this time.

740
01:14:08,157 --> 01:14:09,749
Oh, Mr. Fred.

741
01:14:09,925 --> 01:14:12,826
Everything's all right at the airport.
How's the house?

742
01:14:12,995 --> 01:14:17,364
Look, the American tourists
from the other hotels.

743
01:14:18,901 --> 01:14:20,300
I persuaded them to come here.

744
01:14:20,469 --> 01:14:23,597
That's great, and they all look as if
they could pay their checks.

745
01:14:23,773 --> 01:14:27,140
- Good day, Senhorita Belinha.
- Good day, Senhor Vianna.

746
01:14:27,309 --> 01:14:32,941
I came to express my sympathy...
My best wishes to your dear father.

747
01:14:33,115 --> 01:14:36,243
Thank you. I will take you to him.

748
01:14:36,786 --> 01:14:40,278
Not many people here
for a grand opening.

749
01:14:51,100 --> 01:14:53,500
Nice beach you have here.
That's what I always say.

750
01:14:53,669 --> 01:14:57,230
There's nothing like a nice beach.
We have nice beaches at home too.

751
01:14:57,406 --> 01:14:59,897
We have Rockaway Beach
and we have Revere Beach.

752
01:15:00,309 --> 01:15:02,300
- Check your package, sir?
- It's my medicine.

753
01:15:02,478 --> 01:15:04,207
- Check your...
- My lunch.

754
01:15:04,380 --> 01:15:06,712
- Check...
- Am-scray.

755
01:15:07,449 --> 01:15:08,473
How do you do?

756
01:15:09,218 --> 01:15:11,686
- What are all these packages?
- It's my laundry.

757
01:15:11,854 --> 01:15:13,287
This is a present.

758
01:15:14,456 --> 01:15:19,985
Oh, no, no, no.
I insist that she must be checked.

759
01:15:20,429 --> 01:15:23,296
We had a hard time getting her asleep.

760
01:15:25,100 --> 01:15:28,797
I am a patient man,
but this is beyond endurance.

761
01:15:28,971 --> 01:15:32,771
Who are all these strange people
with those bundles, my dear Carlos?

762
01:15:32,942 --> 01:15:36,639
Why, they're guests
of the hotel, my dear Alfredo.

763
01:15:37,379 --> 01:15:40,177
Where is Roger?
It's time for him to lead the flight.

764
01:15:40,349 --> 01:15:42,715
- I don't know. I haven't seen him.
- Senhor Julio.

765
01:15:42,885 --> 01:15:46,218
The young American requested me
to give you this, this and this.

766
01:15:46,388 --> 01:15:49,050
Thank you. Pardon me.

767
01:15:49,258 --> 01:15:51,988
"Dear Julio, this one is on me.

768
01:15:52,161 --> 01:15:57,030
You can fly as well as I can,
so you lead the parade and be the hero.

769
01:15:58,133 --> 01:16:01,591
I'm taking a plane down to Buenos Aires.
So long, Roger.

770
01:16:01,770 --> 01:16:05,171
P.S. Why don't you marry the girl?"

771
01:16:05,541 --> 01:16:07,133
- What shall I do?
- Do?

772
01:16:07,309 --> 01:16:11,905
Do exactly as he says and you'll be doing
everybody a favor, particularly that P.S. Part.

773
01:16:12,081 --> 01:16:14,413
"Why don't you marry the girl?"

774
01:16:15,017 --> 01:16:18,248
- Elope. That's it. You and Belinha elope.
- Elope?

775
01:16:18,420 --> 01:16:20,513
- Yeah.
- In Brazil we do not elope.

776
01:16:20,689 --> 01:16:23,180
It's against the law. It's bad taste.

777
01:16:23,359 --> 01:16:27,090
In Brazil it takes two weeks
to be respectably married.

778
01:16:27,763 --> 01:16:30,926
Listen, I've heard somewhere,
and what's more I believe it...

779
01:16:31,100 --> 01:16:34,968
...that the pilot of a plane is exactly like
the captain of a transatlantic liner.

780
01:16:35,137 --> 01:16:37,037
Twelve miles out of port
he can marry you.

781
01:16:37,206 --> 01:16:40,107
As soon as this party's over,
you grab Belinha and a plane...

782
01:16:40,276 --> 01:16:42,335
...and put an end to all of this nonsense.

783
01:16:42,511 --> 01:16:44,411
Come on, Julio, use your Brazil nut.

784
01:16:51,420 --> 01:16:56,414
What a pity it is
that you cannot have some entertainment.

785
01:16:56,725 --> 01:16:59,558
With such a distinguished guest as you,
Senhor Vianna...

786
01:16:59,728 --> 01:17:01,889
...there is no need for anything else.

787
01:17:17,613 --> 01:17:19,945
- Look.
- Oh, look.

788
01:17:28,958 --> 01:17:32,416
I trust, my dear Carlos,
you are not doing anything...

789
01:17:32,594 --> 01:17:35,062
...which might offend the authorities.

790
01:17:35,230 --> 01:17:38,757
I trust not, dear Alfredo.

791
01:18:35,491 --> 01:18:38,153
Roger, what are you doing here?

792
01:18:38,327 --> 01:18:41,819
Well, Julio's leading the planes. I'm...

793
01:18:42,998 --> 01:18:44,795
I'm going away.

794
01:18:44,967 --> 01:18:47,731
- You're going away?
- Yeah.

795
01:18:49,671 --> 01:18:52,572
Belinha, I thought everything
would work out for us...

796
01:18:53,342 --> 01:18:56,038
...but things are different
down here in Brazil...

797
01:18:56,211 --> 01:18:58,202
...and I realize now that...

798
01:18:58,881 --> 01:19:01,076
...well, you never could belong to me.

799
01:19:01,884 --> 01:19:04,409
Yes, Roger, you're right.

800
01:19:04,686 --> 01:19:08,349
Here we belong to our families
and our promises.

801
01:19:08,524 --> 01:19:13,086
Even though all we want in the world
is beautiful, crazy happiness.

802
01:19:16,865 --> 01:19:20,460
I guess I should have checked out
when I first learned about Julio.

803
01:19:21,937 --> 01:19:23,962
So...

804
01:19:24,873 --> 01:19:26,397
Goodbye.

805
01:19:27,609 --> 01:19:29,270
Goodbye.

806
01:20:11,120 --> 01:20:13,884
- Any of you fellows like music?
- Sure.

807
01:20:14,056 --> 01:20:16,650
Well, let's tear it wide open.

808
01:20:37,379 --> 01:20:39,370
- Are you ready, boys?
- Ready.

809
01:20:39,548 --> 01:20:40,947
Take it.

810
01:20:44,786 --> 01:20:48,586
<i>An old sailor in old times</i>
<i>Would sing an old song</i>

811
01:20:48,757 --> 01:20:53,057
<i>Rolling down to Rio by the sea</i>

812
01:20:53,228 --> 01:20:57,130
<i>A young sailor in these times</i>
<i>Would sing a new song</i>

813
01:20:57,299 --> 01:21:01,030
<i>Flying down to Rio, come with me</i>

814
01:21:01,203 --> 01:21:05,196
<i>Where the lovely Brazilian ladies</i>
<i>Will catch your eye</i>

815
01:21:05,374 --> 01:21:10,209
<i>By the light of a million stars</i>
<i>In the evening sky</i>

816
01:21:10,379 --> 01:21:14,042
<i>My Rio</i>
<i>Rio by the sea-o</i>

817
01:21:14,216 --> 01:21:18,744
<i>Flying down to Rio</i>
<i>Where there's rhythm and rhyme</i>

818
01:21:18,921 --> 01:21:22,254
<i>Say, fella</i>
<i>Twirl that old propeller</i>

819
01:21:22,424 --> 01:21:26,952
<i>We've got to get to Rio</i>
<i>And we've got to make time</i>

820
01:21:27,129 --> 01:21:30,758
<i>You'll love it</i>
<i>Soaring high above it</i>

821
01:21:30,933 --> 01:21:34,699
<i>Looking down on Rio</i>
<i>From a heaven of blue</i>

822
01:21:34,870 --> 01:21:38,772
<i>Send a radio to Rio de Janeiro</i>

823
01:21:38,941 --> 01:21:41,068
<i>With a big hello</i>
<i>Just so they'll know</i>

824
01:21:41,243 --> 01:21:43,734
<i>And stand by there</i>
<i>We'll fly there</i>

825
01:21:44,213 --> 01:21:47,410
<i>My Rio</i>
<i>Everything will be okay</i>

826
01:21:47,583 --> 01:21:51,917
<i>We're singing and winging our way</i>
<i>To you</i>

827
01:25:17,359 --> 01:25:20,419
- The mayor.
- Hey, mayor!

828
01:25:24,866 --> 01:25:28,859
Carlos, Alfredo.
Sit down, gentlemen, please?

829
01:25:30,138 --> 01:25:33,403
My dear, dear Carlos.
A tremendous success.

830
01:25:33,575 --> 01:25:35,600
My congratulations.

831
01:25:35,777 --> 01:25:39,907
I saw the sky writing at Teresópolis,
and I hurried down here at once.

832
01:25:40,115 --> 01:25:43,551
Vianna, you and your colleagues
ought to be very happy.

833
01:25:43,718 --> 01:25:47,449
- Yes?
- You must buy us all champagne.

834
01:25:47,622 --> 01:25:50,216
I insist. I insist.

835
01:25:51,159 --> 01:25:54,458
Oh, very well. Waiter.

836
01:26:13,048 --> 01:26:14,982
Hey, how do I get out of this?

837
01:26:15,250 --> 01:26:17,741
What's the combination?

838
01:26:20,188 --> 01:26:23,351
- Come, Belinha.
- But where? Why?

839
01:26:30,432 --> 01:26:33,162
This time, I'm taking no chances.

840
01:26:35,036 --> 01:26:38,904
- Julio, where are you taking me?
- On your honeymoon.

841
01:26:39,074 --> 01:26:41,099
Don't be silly. I'm not married.

842
01:26:41,276 --> 01:26:43,471
You will be before you know it.

843
01:27:28,757 --> 01:27:30,418
Can you legally marry people?

844
01:27:30,592 --> 01:27:32,822
Well, yes, if they're fools enough
to ask for it.

845
01:27:32,994 --> 01:27:34,393
Fine.

846
01:27:42,070 --> 01:27:44,971
- Is this the young lady?
- Yes.

847
01:27:49,077 --> 01:27:52,240
- And this is the young man.
- Oh, fine.

848
01:27:52,414 --> 01:27:56,407
Roger, her happiness is my happiness.

849
01:28:03,024 --> 01:28:04,582
Good luck.

850
01:28:22,177 --> 01:28:24,668
Oh, look, look.

851
01:28:27,048 --> 01:28:29,539
Look, here comes Julio.

852
01:28:30,285 --> 01:28:34,449
Gosh, that gal don't care
who she gets thrown out of what.

853
01:28:51,640 --> 01:28:53,631
[ENGLISH]

